    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello, thanks for the maintenance. I find the snaps very useful for work environments where otherwise installing stable releases on older Ubuntu environments to be very helpful.\n\nIt looks like the snapcraft job is failing: https://launchpad.net/~neovim-snap/neovim-ppa/+snap/nvim-stable\n\nFailure snippet from the [amd64 job](https://launchpadlibrarian.net/851132943/buildlog_snap_ubuntu_jammy_amd64_nvim-stable_BUILDING.txt.gz):\n\n```\n:: + cp '/root/.local/share/nvim/site/parser/*' /build/nvim/parts/treesitter-parsers/install/usr/share/nvim/runtime/parser/\n:: cp: cannot stat '/root/.local/share/nvim/site/parser/*': No such file or directory\n'override-build' in part 'treesitter-parsers' failed with code 1.\n```\n\nThis points to the issue being related to the `treesitter-parsers` part of the job:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim-snap/blob/c7ca66eb8565100462cf02b81dbb3c9e655aabc2/snap/snapcraft.yaml#L114\n\nI'm not familiar with the snap build ecosystem, so having a little trouble / slow to debug. This line did change recently in https://github.com/neovim/neovim-snap/pull/52/changes though.",
